================================================================================
CONCLUSION:
================================================================================
The notebook model trained on 9/13 of the pipeline's val images.
So when we evaluated the notebook checkpoint on the pipeline's val split (Test 2)
and got mIoU=0.93, 9 of those 13 'val' images were images
the model had memorized during training.

Similarly, 9/13 of the notebook's own val images were in
the pipeline's training set.

With 85/15 split on 83 images, ANY random split will have ~85% of another
split's val images in its training set. This is expected and means cross-split
evaluation is measuring memorization, not generalization.
